parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine overheating can cause the motorcycle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The temperature gauge rises into the red zone
the coolant temperature gauge increases
the motorcycle overheats in slow traffic or stop-and-go conditions
the coolant leaks or spills onto the highway
and the motorcycle requires frequent stops to cool down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frame failure can cause the motorcycle to become unstable or lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The frame cracks or breaks
the engine drops to the highway
and the steering becomes affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The wobbly handlebar can cause the motorcycle to become unstable or difficult to control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The handlebar wobbles or shakes while riding.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front tire cupping can cause the motorcycle to vibrate or become unstable, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The front tire becomes cupped or worn unevenly
causing vibration while riding.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking or failure of the motorcycle frame can cause the rear of the bike to separate, leading to loss of control and potential accidents, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Cracking or breaking of the frame
often near the welds
particularly on the lower cross member; uneven tire wear; bike handling irregularities; and potential separation of the rear suspension.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front end wobble/vibration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially when braking or cornering.
symptoms: Front end wobbles or vibrates at low speeds (30-40 mph)
cupping of front tire
excessive front tire wear
unsteady braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective steering head bearing can cause front end wobble/vibration, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Front end wobbles or vibrates at low speeds (30-40 mph)
cupping of front tire
excessive front tire wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension adjustment motor can cause the motorcycle to not lift properly, affecting ride quality and handling.
symptoms: Rear suspension adjustment motor does not engage until the indicator display reaches 7 or 8
resulting in delayed or no suspension lift.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fracture of the axle and detachment of tires can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Axle fractures
tires detach from the trailer
loss of control.
